         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">26/6/83. ¶  ¶ I need not say, dear Mr Best, that I will be happy to see the members of the Field-Naturalists Club at the "Herbarium"; and as you wish me to mention an afternoon of Saturday in July, I ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.06.26b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Dudley Best</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">012-035, Field Naturalists Club of Victoria, Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation: 'Ans[were]d 5/7/83'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>26/6/83.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I need not say, dear Mr Best, that I will be happy to see the members of the Field-Naturalists Club at the "Herbarium"; and as you wish me to mention an afternoon of Saturday in July, I would suggest that of the 21st. It would be well, to mention, in the Circular not Museum but "Herbarium", — because a real botanic Museum was never formed for the general public; that portion of my collection, which was to commence the Museum of vegetable products, having gone to the technologic Museum in 1867; so that only one room since 1857 remained ever since for Museum-purposes, and that contains the "herbarium".<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's labels at this date used 'PHYTOLOGIC MUSEUM OF MELBOURNE'; in the report of its meeting of 9 July the Club reminded members of the visit to the 'National Botanical Herbarium'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on 21 July<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 13 July 1883, p. 3).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I shall be personally in attendance on the Members of the Club, if the 21. July should prove a convenient day for their meeting.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
